/\* /index.html 200

# when a user navigates to https://miette-frontend.onrender.com/feed or refreshes the page on any route, Render looks for a file called feed in the built output — which doesn't exist

# this redirect rule tells Render to serve index.html for any path and return a 200 status, letting React Router handle the routing on the client side

# without this, every direct URL access or page refresh returns a 404.
